    "finalTextLength": 2539,
    "finalText": "You need a tighter operating backbone. Right now, evidence points to recurring headaches: backlog on mail/tax/admin, missed or late document handling, and too much reliance on memory or side conversations for follow-up. Here's what will close those gaps:\n\n**1. Weekly Operating Cadence**\n- Standard, non-optional weekly meetings to triage all inbound mail, admin, and tax docs.\n- Every open item gets an owner, a next action, and a due date—visible to leadership.\n- Clear escalation rules when things sit unreviewed.\n\n**2. Centralized Intake and Tracking**\n- One list for all open operational and admin issues—fed by email, meetings, and Teams.\n- Standard fields for owner, status, due date, and blockers.\n- Real-time visibility for leadership; nothing falls through the cracks.\n\n**3. Document Control/Audit Readiness**\n- Systematic scanning, naming, and filing of critical docs: mail, pay apps, invoices, and tax.\n- Consistent conventions for all stored documents.\n- Regular reconciliation of invoices and milestone schedules before payment approval.\n- Audit trail built in up front—not as an afterthought.\n\n**4. Explicit Handoffs**\n- Written, not just verbal, handoffs for admin, finance, and project transitions.\n- Owner and “done” criteria defined every time.\n- Short, written meeting summaries after key sessions to lock in commitments.\n\n**5. Marketing/External Reporting Workflow**\n- Repeatable production process for any outgoing reports (owner, BD, project performance).\n- Pre-set deadlines and pre-defined approval chains to stop last-minute scrambles.\n- One accountable person for assembling and distributing all external comms.\n\n**6. Milestone/Schedule Coordination**\n- Ongoing review of live schedules versus milestones—feeds into pay app/invoice review.\n- Issues flagged *before* they delay delivery or payment.\n- Integration between schedule, finance, and field updates (not handled in silos).\n\n**Operational Risks Right Now**\n- Admin backlog risk: recurring need to \"clean up\" mail and doc piles.\n- Document/audit risk: evidence of missed items and inconsistent organization.\n- Follow-up risk: some action items go quiet unless hunted individually.\n- Visibility risk: leaders can’t see all outstanding tasks in one place.\n\n**Priority Move**\nSet up a single, recurring weekly review covering admin, finance, tax, project milestone status, and overdue action items. The output: one actionable list with names, due dates, and blockers.\n\nIf you want, I can summarize this as a 1-page executive operating model—just say the word.",
